  <h1>Tax compliance calendar FY 2026-27 (all laws)</h1>
  <div class="byline">
    <span class="av">SR</span><b>Written by a Chartered Accountant</b>
    <span class="sep"></span><span>NumberIQ Editorial</span>
    <span class="sep"></span><span>Last reviewed June 2026</span>
    <span class="sep"></span><span>5 min read</span>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="divide"></div>

<article class="prose read">
  <p class="answer-first lead"><b>The key recurring compliance deadlines for FY 2026-27 are: TDS deposit by the 7th, GST returns by the 11th/20th, TDS returns and advance tax quarterly, the GST annual return by 31 December, and income-tax filings during the year.</b> Use the interactive calendar to filter by law and export deadlines.</p>

  <div class="toc"><b>On this page</b><a href="#s0">Monthly deadlines</a> &middot; <a href="#s1">Quarterly and annual</a> &middot; <a href="#s2">MCA deadlines</a> &middot; <a href="#s3">Use the interactive calendar</a></div>

  <!-- ADSENSE SLOT 1 — activate after approval -->

  <h2 id="s0">Monthly deadlines</h2>
<div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Compliance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>7th</td><td>TDS / TCS deposit (Challan 281)</td></tr><tr><td>10th</td><td>GSTR-7 (TDS) / GSTR-8 (TCS)</td></tr><tr><td>11th</td><td>GSTR-1 (monthly)</td></tr><tr><td>13th</td><td>GSTR-6 (ISD) / IFF (QRMP)</td></tr><tr><td>20th</td><td>GSTR-3B (monthly)</td></tr><tr><td>22nd/24th</td><td>GSTR-3B (QRMP, state-wise)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

  <h2 id="s1">Quarterly and annual</h2>
<div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Compliance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>15 Jun/Sep/Dec/Mar</td><td>Advance tax instalments</td></tr><tr><td>31 May / 31 Jul / 31 Oct / 31 Jan</td><td>TDS returns (Q4/Q1/Q2/Q3)</td></tr><tr><td>30 Sep</td><td>Tax audit report (3CD)</td></tr><tr><td>31 Jul / 31 Oct / 30 Nov</td><td>ITR (non-audit / audit / TP)</td></tr><tr><td>31 Dec</td><td>GST annual return (GSTR-9/9C)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

  <h2 id="s2">MCA deadlines</h2>
<ul><li><b>DPT-3</b> &mdash; 30 June (return of deposits).</li><li><b>DIR-3 KYC</b> &mdash; 30 September.</li><li><b>AOC-4 / MGT-7</b> &mdash; within 30 / 60 days of the AGM.</li><li><b>LLP Form 11</b> (30 May) and <b>Form 8</b> (30 October).</li></ul>

  <h2 id="s3">Use the interactive calendar</h2>
<p>The dates above are not automatically extended on holidays. Track them in the <a href="../due-date-calendar.html">NumberIQ due-date calendar</a>, which lets you filter by GST/IT/TDS/MCA and export the deadlines to your own calendar (.ics). <span class="verify">VERIFY</span> any CBIC/CBDT/MCA extensions.</p>

  <div class="faq">
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <details><summary>What are the main monthly tax deadlines?</summary><p>TDS deposit by the 7th, GSTR-7/8 by the 10th, GSTR-1 by the 11th, and GSTR-3B by the 20th (22nd/24th for QRMP).</p></details>
    <details><summary>When is the GST annual return due?</summary><p>GSTR-9/9C is due by 31 December following the financial year.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Are due dates extended on holidays?</summary><p>Not automatically &mdash; unless the relevant department notifies an extension, the stated date applies, so file ahead of weekends and holidays.</p></details>
  </div>

  <!-- ADSENSE SLOT 2 — activate after approval -->

  <div class="key-takeaways"><h2>Key takeaways</h2>
    <ul><li>TDS deposit 7th; GSTR-1 11th; GSTR-3B 20th.</li><li>Advance tax 15 Jun/Sep/Dec/Mar; TDS returns quarterly.</li><li>Tax audit 30 Sep; ITR 31 Jul/31 Oct/30 Nov; GSTR-9 31 Dec.</li><li>Track and export everything via the interactive calendar.</li></ul>
  </div>

